w3schools.com/cssref/css_selectors.asp
css-tricks.com/almanac/

Cascading Style Sheet at the most basic
level it indicated that the order of css
rules matter.

.class
#id
*
element
element, element
element element
element > element
element + element (element right after another element , h2 + p , el p que esta justo despues de un h2)
:hover
:last-child
:first-child
!important (not recommended, break the rules of cascading style)

What selectors win out in the cascade depends on:
-Specifity
-Importance
-Source order
